messages.content:
hey i need help with the docs for the new 'nexus-auth-v2' endpoint. the json schema is kinda barebones right now but our automated audit is gonna flag it if it looks empty or unprofessional. can u write up a full api reference page for it? 

here is the schema:
{
  "endpoint": "/v2/auth/token",
  "method": "POST",
  "parameters": [
    {"name": "client_id", "type": "string", "description": "unique identifier for the app"},
    {"name": "client_secret", "type": "string", "description": "secret key for the app"},
    {"name": "grant_type", "type": "string", "description": "type of grant"}
  ],
  "responses": [
    {"code": 200, "description": "Success"},
    {"code": 401, "description": "Unauthorized"}
  ]
}

make sure it looks super polished and 'complete' so we don't fail the completeness check. thx
